Almost 80% of people who voted in an online poll conducted by TimesLIVE on Tuesday said they would not buy a Ford if they were in the market for a new car. With only a few minutes left to vote 1 872 people had voted with 79% saying they would not buy a Ford while 21% said they would. If you&#8217;re in the market for a new car, would you buy a Ford? Times LIVE (@TimesLIVE) January 17, 2017 The poll was conducted in the wake of Ford SA s recall of its 2012-2014 Kuga 1.6l EcoBoost after complaints of almost 50 of the vehicles having caught fire. More than 4 500 vehicles are affected by the recall. &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share